    pearls: ["hs-CRP >3 mg/L doubles cardiovascular risk independent of LDL cholesterol -- it should be part of comprehensive cardiovascular risk assessment alongside lipid panel and Framingham/ASCVD risk score","The Mediterranean diet is the best-studied anti-inflammatory dietary pattern, reducing hs-CRP, IL-6, and cardiovascular events (PREDIMED trial) -- it is a first-line lifestyle intervention","Regular exercise produces anti-inflammatory effects through myokine release (IL-6 from muscle acts as anti-inflammatory signal during exercise, unlike its pro-inflammatory role when chronically elevated from adipose tissue)","Visceral adipose tissue is the primary source of chronic systemic inflammation in metabolic syndrome -- waist circumference is a better predictor of inflammatory risk than BMI alone","Statins reduce hs-CRP by 15-30% independently of their LDL-lowering effects, contributing to the 'pleiotropic' cardiovascular benefit demonstrated in the JUPITER trial","Chronic inflammation and depression have a bidirectional relationship: inflammatory cytokines reduce serotonin synthesis via the IDO-kynurenine pathway, while depression itself increases inflammatory markers","Obstructive sleep apnea is an underrecognized driver of chronic systemic inflammation: intermittent hypoxia activates NF-kappaB in multiple tissues; CPAP therapy reduces hs-CRP and cardiovascular risk"],
