    pearls: ["Alcohol abuse is the #1 cause of chronic pancreatitis (60-70%); complete abstinence slows disease progression and improves pain in 50% of patients -- this is the single most important intervention","Fecal elastase-1 <200 mcg/g confirms exocrine insufficiency; steatorrhea does not appear until >90% of lipase secretion is lost, meaning significant malabsorption precedes clinical steatorrhea","PERT must be taken with the FIRST BITE of food at every meal and snack -- taking it before or after the meal dramatically reduces efficacy; if inadequate response, add a PPI to prevent acid destruction of enzymes in the duodenum","Type 3c (pancreatogenic) diabetes is uniquely dangerous because BOTH insulin and glucagon are deficient -- hypoglycemia risk is much higher than in type 1 or type 2 diabetes; set relaxed glycemic targets (HbA1c 7-8%) and always prescribe a glucagon emergency kit","Chronic pancreatitis pain often 'burns out' in late-stage disease as acinar tissue is completely replaced by fibrosis -- paradoxically, pain may improve as exocrine insufficiency worsens","Chronic pancreatitis confers a 3-5% lifetime risk of pancreatic adenocarcinoma -- any change in pain character, new-onset or worsening diabetes, or rapid weight loss in a previously stable patient should trigger urgent imaging","Pancreatic calcifications on CT are pathognomonic for chronic pancreatitis and distinguish it from acute pancreatitis or pancreatic cancer; EUS with Rosemont criteria is the most sensitive test for early disease before calcifications develop"],
